  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points; parameter sensitivity to impeller tip clearance, inlet angle, and volute geometry was explored via Latin-hypercube sampling (n=512). Results confirmed that RH remained below 1.0 across the design envelope, supporting the Accepted decision.",
