      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — all 5 operating points",
      "description": "Computational velocity profiles compared against particle image velocimetry measurements at Q=2,3,4,5,6 L/min. Area-weighted RMS error < 8% at all stations. The UQ campaign (Latin-hypercube, n=512) confirmed that model-form uncertainty contributes less than 4% to RH variance; geometric tolerances dominate. Validation activities support credibility at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-rh-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against in-vitro bench data",
      "description": "Predicted RH index compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements (ASTM F1841 protocol) across the 5 operating conditions. All predicted RH values within 15% of measured values; worst-case predicted RH = 0.87 (< 1.0 acceptance criterion). Sensitivity of RH to blood viscosity and shear-stress power-law exponent was explored narratively during the UQ campaign and documented in the technical report."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/grid-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid convergence index study — discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M elements). GCI < 2.3% for all QoIs at the fine mesh level. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Fine mesh selected for all production runs."
    }
  ],
